definition:
εἰλικρινής, -ές, 
 [in LXX: Wi 72^ kB * ;] 
unalloyed, pure (Lat. sincerus; see DCG, ii, 635a); 
  (a) of unmixed substances; 
   (b) of abstract ideas; 
   (with) of ethical purity: Php.1:10, 2Pe.3:1.†
 SYN.: ἁγνός (which see), καθαρός, cf. Tr., Syn.: §lxxxv; DB, iv, 176a; Cremer, 378; Westc. on 1Jn.3:3. (AS)
